      "writtenOn": "2026-06-22T07:19:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "`kinds :\u003d i.kinds` aliases the backing array, so this `slices.Delete` mutates (and zeroes) `i.kinds` in place. Since items are interned, the same `*itemType` can be generated more than once, and the second call sees the corrupted slice. `generate` should be pure.\n\nRepro (OpenAPI):\n\n\t#A: null | string\n\t#B: null | string\n\ta: #A\n\tb: #B\n\nA renders correctly as `anyOf:[{enum:[null]},{type:\"string\"}]`, but B\u0027s null branch becomes `{type:\"\"}`. Fix: `slices.Delete(slices.Clone(kinds), j, j+1)`. Worth a fixture with two identical null-bearing defs to cover it.",
      "revId": "ff956ffb814a7079b6eeee3ca99b4b7f0a1ff5b6",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
